      'CO-DEFENDANTS: Mark Meadows (Chief of Staff), Rudy Giuliani, John Eastman (coup memo), Jeffrey Clark (DOJ official), Sidney Powell, Jenna Ellis, and others. Several have pled guilty including Powell, Ellis, Kenneth Chesebro, and Scott Hall.',
      'GUILTY PLEAS: Sidney Powell pled guilty to reduced charges and agreed to cooperate. Kenneth Chesebro pled guilty to conspiracy. Jenna Ellis pled guilty to aiding and abetting false statements. Scott Hall pled guilty to conspiracy charges. These deals may produce testimony against remaining defendants.',
      'CASE STATUS: The sprawling case faces legal challenges and delay tactics. Some defendants seek removal to federal court. The case has been complicated by allegations about DA Willis personal relationship with special prosecutor Nathan Wade, which resulted in Wades resignation but Willis remaining on the case.',
