      'MARKET-MOVING TWEETS: Trump\'s tweets moved markets billions of dollars. Advance knowledge of tariff announcements, company attacks, or policy shifts enabled insider trading. A 2019 SEC complaint alleged suspicious trading before Trump tweets. No charges resulted despite documented patterns.',
      'TARIFF FRONT-RUNNING: Tariff announcements created massive volatility. Carl Icahn allegedly made over $30 million shorting steel companies before tariff announcements (he denied wrongdoing). The lack of insider trading investigation was notable given the documented pattern of leaks.',
      'HISTORICAL SECURITIES VIOLATIONS: Trump Hotels & Casino Resorts was fined by SEC for misleading earnings reports (2002, $750K penalty). Trump overstated casino earnings to pump stock price while insiders sold. This established pattern continues.',
