      'PRUITT RESIGNATION: After 14 months of cascading scandals, Pruitt resigned in July 2018. Despite the obvious corruption, Trump praised him and blamed "Radical Left Democrats" for his departure.',
      'RYAN ZINKE - INTERIOR: Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke spent $139,000 on new office doors, chartered flights to events near his Montana property, and used his position to benefit a real estate project involving Halliburton\'s chairman.',
      'ZINKE RESIGNATION: Zinke resigned in December 2018 facing multiple investigations including a criminal referral for lying to investigators. His departure came just before Democrats took the House.',
      'MNUCHIN TRAVEL: Treasury Secretary Steve Mnuchin requested military aircraft for his honeymoon in Europe. He and his wife drew criticism for posing with freshly printed money like Bond villains.',
      'WILBUR ROSS: Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross allegedly stole millions from business partners according to Forbes. He maintained stock holdings creating conflicts of interest and fell asleep in meetings.',
      'BEN CARSON: HUD Secretary Ben Carson ordered a $31,000 dining set for his office. He initially blamed his wife. His son helped arrange deals for HUD grantees, creating ethics concerns.',
