      'JANUARY 6 COMMITTEE INTERVIEW: Thomas agreed to a voluntary interview with the January 6 Committee. She answered questions about her activities but denied doing anything wrong and refused to say the 2020 election was legitimate.',
      'RECUSAL REFUSAL: Despite his wife\'s involvement in the events, Justice Clarence Thomas refused to recuse from January 6-related cases. He was the sole dissent when the Court rejected Trump\'s attempt to block White House records.',
      'EASTMAN CONNECTION: Ginni Thomas had communications with John Eastman, author of the coup memos. Eastman had clerked for Clarence Thomas and remained close to both. The connections between coup planners and the Thomas household were extensive.',
      'CONFLICT OF INTEREST: Federal law requires judges to recuse when their spouse has an interest in a case. Ginni Thomas\'s direct involvement in the election subversion attempt created an obvious conflict that Clarence Thomas ignored.',
      'CLARENCE THOMAS LONE DISSENT: In Trump v. Thompson, the Supreme Court rejected Trump\'s attempt to shield White House records from the January 6 Committee. Clarence Thomas was the only dissenter. Those records revealed his wife\'s texts.',
      'ETHICS QUESTIONS: The Thomas situation highlighted the absence of a binding ethics code for the Supreme Court. Unlike lower court judges, Supreme Court justices answer to no one on ethics questions.',
      'NO CONSEQUENCES: Despite the revelations, Clarence Thomas faced no formal consequences. Republicans blocked attempts to investigate. The conflict of interest was simply ignored.',
      'ONGOING INFLUENCE: Ginni Thomas remains active in conservative politics. She runs a consulting firm and attends activist events. Her access to her husband\'s position continues to raise corruption concerns.',
