      'PRESIDENTIAL RECORDS ACT: The Presidential Records Act requires preservation of official communications. Using RNC servers and deleting emails violated this law. But the Bush administration faced no prosecution.',
      'WHO USED OUTSIDE EMAIL: Users included Karl Rove, who conducted extensive official business on RNC accounts. Other senior officials used the accounts for communications they wanted to hide from oversight.',
