      'FAUCI\'S TESTIMONY: Dr. Anthony Fauci testified that NIH did not fund gain-of-function research at WIV. Later documents revealed this was at minimum misleading. The definition of gain-of-function became central to the dispute.',
      'OVERSIGHT FAILURES: NIH lacked effective oversight mechanisms for research conducted at foreign labs. EcoHealth failed to file required progress reports for years. The system allowed dangerous research without proper monitoring.',
      'MORATORIUM CIRCUMVENTION: A 2014-2017 moratorium on gain-of-function research may have been circumvented through definitional games. Research that would have been paused if conducted at U.S. labs continued in China.',
      'ECOHEALTH DEBARMENT: In 2024, HHS debarred EcoHealth Alliance and Peter Daszak from federal funding for failures in grant management and oversight. This came years after the problems were identified.',
      'BIOSAFETY CONCERNS: Intelligence agencies identified WIV biosafety concerns before the pandemic. Researchers reportedly became ill with COVID-like symptoms in fall 2019. These warnings weren\'t adequately addressed.',
      'LAB LEAK RELEVANCE: If COVID-19 emerged from WIV research, U.S. funding of that research would be catastrophically significant. Even if the virus emerged naturally, the funding relationship demands scrutiny.',
      'TRANSPARENCY FAILURES: NIH and EcoHealth resisted releasing documents about the research. Information emerged through FOIA requests and congressional investigations rather than voluntary disclosure.',
      'REFORM NEEDS: The episode revealed gaps in oversight of international research on dangerous pathogens. Reforms are needed regardless of COVID-19\'s origin to prevent future risks.',
