    summary: 'EcoHealth Alliance, led by Peter Daszak, served as a conduit for U.S. funding to Wuhan Institute of Virology. When questions arose about COVID-19\'s origins, Daszak organized a letter dismissing lab leak as "conspiracy theory" while concealing his conflicts of interest. Investigations revealed inadequate oversight, unreported research, and efforts to manipulate the origin narrative.',
    content: [
      'PETER DASZAK: EcoHealth Alliance president Peter Daszak built close relationships with WIV researchers, particularly bat coronavirus expert Shi Zhengli. He funneled NIH grants to WIV for chimeric coronavirus research.',
      'LANCET LETTER: In February 2020, Daszak organized a letter in The Lancet condemning lab leak "conspiracy theories." He concealed his role in organizing it and his direct conflict of interest as WIV funder.',
      'ORCHESTRATED NARRATIVE: Emails revealed Daszak strategized to avoid association with the Lancet letter to give it more credibility. He wanted it to appear as independent scientists defending Chinese colleagues rather than interested parties protecting themselves.',
      'CONFLICT OF INTEREST: Daszak was appointed to WHO\'s COVID-19 origin investigation team despite his obvious conflict. He had to recuse himself from Lancet\'s commission for the same reason. His involvement compromised early investigations.',
      'GRANT MISMANAGEMENT: EcoHealth failed to file required progress reports to NIH for years. When reports emerged, they revealed research results that should have triggered additional oversight. The organization operated with minimal accountability.',
      'UNREPORTED EXPERIMENTS: NIH eventually acknowledged that EcoHealth-funded research at WIV produced more transmissible coronaviruses. This met gain-of-function definitions but wasn\'t reported as required.',
      'HHS DEBARMENT: In 2024, the Department of Health and Human Services debarred EcoHealth Alliance and Daszak from federal funding. The debarment cited grant management failures and inadequate oversight of WIV research.',
      'DEFUSE PROPOSAL: A rejected DARPA proposal called DEFUSE planned to insert furin cleavage sites into bat coronaviruses at WIV. SARS-CoV-2 has such a site. Whether similar research occurred outside DEFUSE remains unknown.',
      'ONGOING STONEWALLING: EcoHealth and Daszak have resisted document production and full transparency about WIV collaboration. Congressional investigators faced obstruction in obtaining complete records.',
      'SCIENTIFIC INTEGRITY: The Lancet letter and Daszak\'s manipulation of origin debates damaged scientific credibility. By framing legitimate questions as "conspiracy theory," he poisoned discourse and delayed investigation.',
    ],
    tags: ['EcoHealth Alliance', 'Peter Daszak', 'Wuhan', 'Lab Leak', 'Conflict of Interest', 'Scientific Integrity'],
