      '2008 SWEETHEART DEAL: When Florida prosecutors built a case, Epstein received a federal non-prosecution agreement arranged by Alexander Acosta (later Trump\'s Labor Secretary). He served 13 months with work release for soliciting a minor.',
      'ACOSTA\'S EXPLANATION: Acosta later claimed he was told Epstein "belonged to intelligence." Whether this was a real factor or an excuse, Epstein\'s connections protected him from serious consequences.',
      'DEATH IN CUSTODY: Epstein died in his Manhattan jail cell in August 2019, officially by suicide. Cameras malfunctioned. Guards falsified records. The circumstances invite suspicion about who wanted him silenced.',
      'GHISLAINE MAXWELL: Maxwell, Epstein\'s partner and procurer, was convicted of sex trafficking in 2021 and sentenced to 20 years. Her trial revealed operational details but didn\'t identify most of Epstein\'s clients.',
      'THE UNNAMED: Flight logs and other documents identify many who visited Epstein\'s island. Few have faced consequences. The victims got settlements; the perpetrators got silence.',
      'PRINCE ANDREW: Queen Elizabeth\'s son reached a settlement with Virginia Giuffre after denying her accusations. He was stripped of royal duties but never faced criminal charges.',
      'INSTITUTIONAL FAILURE: Law enforcement, prosecutors, and the media failed to pursue the Epstein network for decades. Powerful connections provided protection that would be unavailable to ordinary criminals.',
