      'MILITARIZATION: The 1033 Program has transferred billions in military equipment to local police. SWAT deployments increased from 3,000/year in the 1980s to 50,000+ today. Military tactics are used for routine drug searches.',
      'FAILED REFORMS: Body cameras have not reduced killings. "Training" programs show no improvement. Consent decrees are routinely violated. Without structural changes to qualified immunity, criminal prosecution standards, and union power, reform efforts have failed.',
      'DEFUND MOVEMENT: The 2020 uprising following George Floyd\'s murder generated calls to redirect police funding to social services. Most cities increased police budgets instead. Some cities that cut budgets subsequently restored funding.',
