    summary: 'The Supreme Court\'s Citizens United decision held that corporations have First Amendment rights and can spend unlimited amounts on elections. Combined with related rulings, it opened the floodgates to "dark money" - billions in anonymous spending that has corrupted American politics. The decision was preceded by decades of right-wing legal strategy.',
