      'THE REALITY: Independent expenditures are not truly independent. Super PACs coordinate with campaigns through shared consultants, public signals, and barely-legal workarounds. The distinction is fiction.',
      'DARK MONEY: 501(c)(4) "social welfare" organizations can spend on elections without disclosing donors. Billions have flowed through organizations like Crossroads GPS, Americans for Prosperity, and Majority Forward.',
      'THE NUMBERS: Outside spending exploded from $750 million in 2008 to $7 billion in 2020. Dark money grew from $100 million in 2010 to $1+ billion in 2020. Most benefits Republicans, but Democrats have caught up.',
      'JUDICIAL SELECTION: Leonard Leo used Federalist Society networks to channel $250+ million in dark money to pack courts with conservative judges, including the Citizens United majority itself.',
      'LEGISLATIVE CAPTURE: Dark money groups write model legislation through ALEC. They fund primary challengers against insufficiently loyal politicians. They reward obstruction and punish compromise.',
      'THE KOCH NETWORK: Charles Koch built a political network spending hundreds of millions per election cycle through a web of nonprofits, PACs, and advocacy organizations. The network has shaped tax policy, climate denial, and deregulation.',
      'ATTEMPTED REFORM: Constitutional amendments to overturn Citizens United have been introduced but never passed. States have passed disclosure laws that courts have often blocked.',
      'FOREIGN MONEY: Dark money\'s anonymity creates pathways for foreign influence. The NRA was investigated for Russian money. Shell companies can obscure ultimate sources.',
      'DEMOCRACY DAMAGED: Studies show policies favor donor preferences over public opinion. Voter trust in government has collapsed. The link between money and political outcomes is clear.',
